    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-24T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-24T23:00:00-05:00" n="1006"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1006">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.417/1163: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-25T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 25, 1941—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>617. Your 1389, September 5, 1 p.m., fur seal agreement. The Department hopes
                    that you can arrange at an early date to meet the Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    and ascertain from him the general views and intentions of the Japanese
                    Government with respect to the proposals contained in the Department’s 475,
                    August 7, 2 p.m.</p>
                <p>For your information, the time element is becoming increasingly important because
                    of the probability that certain new legislation will be required in this country
                    (possibly paralleling Canadian legislation) for the protection of the fur seal
                    herd of the Pribilof Islands should the Convention of 1911 expire without
                    replacement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
